The paper deals with the computational complexity of a model of tile assembly, which is a topic that falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves geometric concepts and self-assembly, which are relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and theoretical computer science (cs.TC). The use of the pumping lemma, a concept from formal language theory, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
